# Oracle APEX Setup

The implementation consists of three components.

```
Static Content Region
        │
        ▼
JavaScript Global Declaration
        │
        ▼
Execute When Page Loads
```

---

## 1. Static Content Region

Create a **Static Content** region containing:

- Previous Page button
- Page indicator
- Next Page button
- Zoom controls
- Status indicator
- PDF Viewer container

---

## 2. Function and Global Variable Declaration

Create a page-level JavaScript declaration.

This object is responsible for:

- Loading the PDF
- Rendering pages
- Zooming
- Previous / Next navigation
- High DPI rendering
- Status updates

---

## 3. Execute When Page Loads

Load PDF.js from jsDelivr.

Initialize the viewer.

Attach button events.

Load the PDF.

---

# PDF Source

Assign the PDF URL from an APEX item.

Example

```javascript
window.apexPdfViewer.pdfUrl =
    '&P120_ATTACHMENT_ID!JS.';
```

The item should contain a valid Amazon S3 pre-signed URL.

